2) User Profile (V1) — Summary

What it shows
	1.	Header: avatar, display name/@username, bio, small level pill.
	2.	Showcased Badges: up to 5, user-selected.
	3.	11/10 Highlight: exactly one per account (user’s #1).
	4.	Top List: user-curated, ranked (up to 10), clean at any length.
	5.	Social Links: YouTube, Twitch, X (optional).

Read-only for guests: profiles are viewable without auth; editing requires sign-in (added later).

Schema Adds (to existing DB)
	•	user_profiles(user_id, bio, show_level, show_socials, top_list_limit)
	•	user_social_links(user_id, platform in ['youtube','twitch','twitter'], url)
	•	user_toplist(user_id, anime_id, position, note) with unique (user_id, position)
	•	Partial unique index on ratings(user_id) where is_eleven_out_of_ten = true (enforces single 11/10).

Milestones
	•	M1: Read-only profile rendering (badges/11/10/top list/socials).
	•	M2: Editing flows (search add, drag/drop reorder, set 11/10, choose showcased badges, edit socials).
	•	M3: Auth gate + RLS policies.

⸻

3) Feedback & Discovery (recap)
	•	Cadence: combo toast at 3 ratings; quest/badge modals only; daily session summary.
	•	Rails over infinite scroll: finite horizontal rails with end-cards (soft quests: “rate 3 more to unlock”).

⸻

4) Cosmetics & Currency (non-blockchain)

Design chosen: Soft-currency (Stardust) from quests/levels → gacha rolls for off‑chain collectible avatars.
	•	Cosmetic only (no gameplay power).
	•	Pity + shards to reduce RNG frustration.
	•	Visibility: profile, comments/quests mini-flair, album view.
	•	No real-money purchases in MVP → avoids loot-box compliance overhead.

Tables (later): user_wallet, gacha_pool, gacha_item, user_item, gacha_roll, user_pity + Edge Function roll_gacha(pool_id).

⸻

5) MVP Roadmap (execution order)
	1.	Discover rails + Anime detail (Similar by tags).
	2.	Ratings with tag facets + combo feedback.
	3.	Profile V1 (read-only).
	4.	P2P Quest v1 (async, no chat) + XP/badges.
	5.	Soft-currency gacha + cosmetic equip (off-chain).
	6.	Import tool (CSV) + creator lists V1.
	7.	Moderation & spoiler system.
	8.	Co-occurrence recs + notifications.

⸻

6) Locked Decisions (to remember)
	•	Top List cap: up to 10 (must look clean at any length).
	•	11/10: exactly one per account.
	•	Socials: YouTube, Twitch, X.
	•	No blockchain/NFTs — collectibles are off-chain.
	•	iOS-first for MVP.

